  "final_text": "Build succeeded \u2705 \u2014 here's a summary:\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Project** | `BLINKY` |\n| **Configuration** | `Debug` |\n| **Duration** | 4.5 s |\n| **ELF artifact** | `\u2026/GPIO/BLINKY/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/BLINKY.elf` |\n| **Map file** | `\u2026/GPIO/BLINKY/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/BLINKY.map` |\n| **Log** | `\u2026/logs/build-20260522T082812Z.log` |\n\n**Two warnings to note (non-fatal):**\n- `Project: BLINKY doesn't appear to be a CDT project. Skipping...` \u2014 CubeIDE emitted this during the import step but the build still completed and produced an ELF. This typically means the project was already present in the workspace.\n- `No Config matched \"BLINKY/Debug\". Skipping...` \u2014 same benign import-phase warning; the Debug configuration built successfully regardless.\n\nThe ELF is ready to flash. Let me know if you'd like to `stm32 prog flash` it or start a debug session."
